4. K-series trains are much slower (24 hours) and not ideal for a 3-day trip, as they eat into sightseeing time.
5. Consistency with the start-to-target journey isn't critical since the family is flexible (flying there, could take train/flight back).
6. Prioritize flights with lower cost and reasonable timings (e.g., FL348 at 16:16 is ideal for a full last day of sightseeing).

